Score: 0.6
Reasoning: The algorithm is logically correct (it counts distinct repeated-character substrings) but constructs and stores all repeated substrings explicitly, causing O(N^2) time and memory in the worst case. It will pass small and random tests but will TLE/MLE on large adversarial inputs (e.g., all characters the same).
